$\sum_{k \in \text{range } (m + 1)} (2k + 1) = \sum_{k \in \text{range } m} (2k + 1) + (2m + 1)$

The induction hypothesis tells us that $\sum_{k \in \text{range } m} (2k + 1) = m^2$, so we get $m^2 + (2m + 1) = (m + 1)^2$.

